Project made with python to collect, clean, and train a model for object detection on RGBD images.
The model is going to be used to detect rocks and creators in a depth image.
The first step was to turn a video of the depth and rgb image into frames, this was done with an online resorce.
Second, RANSAC was used to create a ground plane that shows any obsticals that might be obove or bellow the ground.
Third, DBSCAN and DGSCAN was used to make labels and bounding boxes for any obsical
Final the model was trained using YOLOv8

# RANSAC
python3 ransac_pipeline.py

# labels and bounding boxes
python3 mask_to_yolo.py \
    --image_dir data/images \
    --mask_dir  data/masks \
    --label_dir data/labels \
    --visualize

# Prep and Splitting data 
python3 prepare_dataset.py \
    --image_dir data/images \
    --label_dir data/labels \
    --output_dir dataset

# Train
python3 train_yolo.py \
    --data dataset/dataset.yaml \
    --model yolov8n.pt \
    --epochs 100 \
    --batch 16 \
    --device cpu


I am using a venv to keep track of python3 and yolo dependensies